title: 820-2879 won't start
message:
This board first had a problem with power dropping on PPBUS_G3H, found a bad trace on current sensing so i soldered a wire between R7050 and R7052 to fix the power dropping.
PPBUS_G3H is 12.59 volt
I have green light.
There has been liquid on the board. Some red points on top of the board around the U7600 area and around the SMC.

What can I check before I call it dead?

title: 820-2879 won't start
message: Resistance to GND on 3V42 and both RTC Xtal pins?

title: 820-2879 won't start
message:
Resistance to groud on
PP3V42_G3H is 122 ohm
XTALIN is 20.7 ohm
XTALOUT is 15.5 ohm

title: 820-2879 won't start
message: If it really is Ohm and not K or M Ohms then your MCP is very dead.

title: 820-2879 won't start
message: MCP is dead, so scrap I would say.
